# Released artifacts and generated registry JSON are byte-addressed content —
# their sha256 digests are recorded in registry/blocks/*.json and verified by
# every `ion-drive add`. Disable EOL translation so a Windows checkout serves
# (and `registry build --check` hashes) exactly the committed bytes.
*/dist/** -text
registry/** -text
schemas/** -text
registries.json -text
registry.config.json -text
# Block READMEs are copied byte-exact into registry/blocks/*.readme.md by
# `registry build` — EOL translation on the sources would make --check drift.
*/README.md -text
badges/** -text
# Vendored block sources are embedded byte-for-byte into packed artifacts
# (`code[].contents`), so EOL translation on a Windows checkout would change
# every artifact digest `registry build` computes.
*/code/** -text
*/test/** -text
